column5: Well I'll be jiggered..  That red face and smile from ear to ear..  I know that cat!  What year was it?  1999?  Anywho, been a long while since that summer at Central Surplus..  Grant!  You lucky sumab***!!  Good to see you alive and well.  Congrats on your PB..  Bunk, another awe inspiring thread.  Catchy title too!!  One of the reason why this place is home.  cheers HD
I sit down at my 'puter, and I see "Another post by Moosebunk"; and think to myself, just how much more can the guy do????? Quite a bit apparently. Thank you for the wonderful, envy inducing read.
Great Report
I really dont see what was so great about it.     hahhaha.     That was wicked man.   Nice job
A trip with Scottydog and the Bunkster. That is something to revel in. I love Grant with his pike, he couldn't have looked happier. You guys slayed them, awesome report on so many different levels.
Awesome report a usual! Some truly impressive 'Gators'.
Great Report Bunk. Looks like you had a good time. I'll talk to you soon.  -Dave
Man...thats a trip and a half!!!  Your reports always make me WAY jealous But I appreciate all the effort you put into them Thanks for the report bud!  Cheers,
Thanks for the bump and words late-comers. lol.  Gives me another chance to relive that great trip while having a late breakfast.
Any time bud,
Bunk,  I've read this great report somewhere on the mighty web and all I can say is...............PRICELESS  Thanks for sharing! Leechman

Absolutely Amazing Fishing T rip  !!!!!!!!  incredible pictures,  and huge fish as well,it sure is fishermens heaven,thanks for the report,you make me feel like i was there,looking forward to the next trip too !!!!...cheers
Simply speechless
I dont think there is carp up there Victor  , Those big pike ate them all ahah.  Love reading your reports man, just some great scenery and some great fish.
Very impressive report, even more impressive Trophy Pike and even more impressive scenery shots orf that turbulent river! Certainly it was a trip of a lifetime. Thanks for sharing.
Thanks for putting so much time and effort into your posts. They take me FAR away from the office..  Excellent stuff  cheers
Gotta be one of the best reports I've ever read! Awesome!!! Awesome!!! Did I mention that your trip looked like it was.........AWESOME!!!

Absolutely Amazing !!!!!!  Your fishing reports are without a doubt the best i have ever read PERIOD. !!!!!   i think they get better everytime,you sure know how to do it up big time,and living way up north,and having all those possibilities,its great !!!  thanks for sharing,looking forward to seeing all that scenery & fish porn again real soon  ,thanks for making me really jelous !!.lol..lol.. cheers
You sure do grow them big up there.  Always look forward to your amazing reports and beautiful pics.
Thanks for sharing, well done.  Dan
Awesome report thanks for taking the time to put it together  Im so jealous
sweet.always look forward to your posts another stellar adventure great job on those gators.only another 10 long months till i return to the great north. your a lucky man im a little jealous.
stellar report man  your my hero
wow!!!!!!!! awesome report!  Cheers!

Seriously -- can I go fishing with you?    Honest to goodness...every one of your posts could be the trip of someone's lifetime....this one was off the charts.  THEN, when we're supposed to be coming down slowly, after all the heavy breathing with those fish....you drop the Hell's Gate / Thunderhouse pics on us?  I was almost in tears -- stopped breathing for a minute, no question. Thanks for sharing!!!!!
Sweet report Drew.  You are one lucky jerk to be able to go on all these trips and fish some great spots.  Great pics.  Joey
MIND BLOWING! SIMPLY MIND BLOWING!
Thanks Gang.   This summer is only just getting started.
Awesome stuff, those are some serious pike!
Great trip log and report. Thanks
Impressive....Sick!
WOW!!!  What a trip and report.  Got to love those snarlin' darlin's
Maybe one of the best reports ever!.. you live my dream!

Thanks for the great read!  Took almost 45 minutes to read but worth it. Excellent writing and great pics;  from James Bay muskeg, arrival at camp, non-stop big walleye and pike, the departure, to great pics of Hells Gate/ Thunderhouse Falls,  all quality and quantity. You should get paid by Field and Stream, OOD, etc... for this great stuff. Thanks for taking all the time creating this post. ehg
Great REPORT! AS ALWAYS!  Man I want to live there LOL!
AMAZING photos once again MB. Now to go back and read the story. You always take me to that happy place.
Amazing story too Bunker. I love that happy place you always take me to!
Holy Crap....  what a report....  made me dizzy!!!  another trip oif a lifetime and wonderfull, as always, report!

Wow...chalk up yet another chapter in "The Many Fishing Adventures of The Mighty Moosebunk"!!!  I would have replied earlier, but I find I like to set up with a coffee in one hand, the children in bed, and no TV on so I can read every word uninterrupted.  This report had me riveted!!!  I have never seen so many big pike in one report before.  The walleye were gorgeous as well. I loved the "about 2 weeks" thing...LOL.  What a great adventure....I can only hope to catch just a glimpse of the kinds of fishing trips that you go on!  Thanks for that....must have taken hours to compose that report...appreciate the effort!!
Excellent report, pics, and fish!!!
.Wow you never fail to amaze us mb.You are the king of posts.  Thank you for showing us heaven.
amazing again! Thanks so much.
Amazing.  "Thank you for showing us heaven. "....I concour.  Thanks you for sharing that wonderful adventure with us!
"Wow" is all I can say right now lol.  Love the report and I'm always so jealous reading them because it is very unlikely that i'll catch ONE fish that's as big as the ones you guys got lol.
Amazing as always Drew. A trip like that makes putting up with the 'squito's bearable.
That was awesome.

Absolutely AMAZING REPORT!!!! those piuctures are icredible!!!! dont know why but apart from the fish pics...my favourite is the close-up of the beetle. What camera do you use?   once again, great report, thanks for sharing.
Another fine treat provided by you.  The pics of Thunderhouse Falls and Hell Gate are amazing.  The first explorers must have been sh*@!$ their pants when they first saw that.
Speechless, simply awesome!!!!!
Speechless!
Kinda makes my rapids look pretty puny, huh?    But I betcha Drew can't wade thru his.  JF
what a trip big pike and eyes simply the best
wow great read....really enjoyed this one, thanks

the fishing up that way is amazing. i can definetly agree.   i've fished primarily the east arm of missinaibi lake , and missinaibi river for years. but those in flight pics of the falls are just breathtaking.  that tea stained water makes it looks crazy.  i had a smile on my face the whole time reading this post.  thanks
Standing ovation from me!
Nice!!!!  :clapping:  :clapping: RF

Drew.............................I get kinda numb reading your reports...........or..............should I say........not really reading them. I forget about the text, and just look at the pictures, whatever they are, of fish or scenery. Both are awesome as usual. Kinda like reading Playboy (it does have good articles in it, HONEST!!), when you are 16 yrs. old,   :lol:  :lol:  Thanks for making me drool, again.

Amazing, unbelievable, fantastic report! Incredible number of large pike, and you're right, the size of the walleyes are astounding for that far north!  (I feel sick to my stomach now, man I wish I could have joined you, but I just couldn't swing it  . I think I know where I'm going next year though  .)

Thanks MB for another good adventure!!  I always read your posts twice. First I start reading then as soon as I see a pictures I scroll down aagain and again, by the 4th picture I completely forget that there is a story attached to it , so I looke at all teh pictures and then start the whole thing again.
Finally got done reading another moosebunk novel and once again glad I took the time to read it end to end.  You never fail to disappoint.  Thanks as always for a great way to start my week.
You actually "read" all of that|?????  :worthy:  :worthy:  I mostly looked at the pictures.
I'm speechless
that was better than an advertisement for any tour operator up there!  Thanks for the photo's.. Got any PROZAC now?
